<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN207-intro">
        <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. veḷimāṉ tuñciyapiṉ avaṉṟampi iḷaveḷimāṉaip paricilkoṭuveṉa avaṉciṟitukoṭuppak koḷḷātu peruñcittiraṉār pāṭiyatu.
        </p>
        <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
        </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN207">
        <lg type="edition"> 
<l>eḻuviṉi neñcañ celkam yārō</l>
<l>paruku vaṉṉa vēṭkai yilvaḻi</l>
<l>yarukiṟ kaṇṭu maṟiyār pōla</l>
<l>vakaṉaku vārā mukaṉaḻi parici</l>
<l>ṟāḷi lāḷar vēḷā rallar</l>
<l>varukeṉa vēṇṭum varicai yōrkkē</l>
<l>peritē yulakam pēṇunar palarē</l>
<l>mīḷi muṉpi ṉāḷi pōla</l>
<l>vuḷḷa muḷḷavin taṭaṅkātu veḷḷeṉa</l>
<l>nōvā tōṉvayiṟ ṟiraṅki</l>
<l>vāyā vaṉkaṉik kulamavaru vōrē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Rise now, heart, we will go. Who [is he]? (1)</l>
<l>Like those who do not know, even if they see up close, (3)</l>
<l>in a way without desire that is like drinking, (2)</l>
<l>men without effort (5ab)</l>
<l>with respect gifts that perish in the mouth to which in inner smile does not come,</l>
<l>	are not rulers. (5cd)</l>
<l>It is necessary to say “you may come” to those with marks of honour. (6)</l>
<l>Vast is the world. Many are those who bestow honour. (7)</l>
<l>– without restraining [our] mind, dying inside, (9a-c)</l>
<l>like the Āḷi with the strength of a commander, (8)</l>
<l>for the sake of an unfit hard fruit to the disturbed, (11)</l>
<l>dried up at the side of one who clearly takes not pains. (9d-10)</l>
</lg>
    </div>
